1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,369
The progressive business knows that how strong it will be five years from now depends not on what it does five years in the future,

2
00:00:08,399 --> 00:00:12,050
but rather on what it does, invests, this year.

3
00:00:12,399 --> 00:00:16,130
Profit comes from only one source—investment.

4
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:18,449
There's a lesson for each of us.

5
00:00:18,639 --> 00:00:26,369
To profit—to get the extra reward above a normal income in the years ahead—we must invest in ourselves.

6
00:00:26,559 --> 00:00:29,650
We must invest to achieve our goals.

7
00:00:30,719 --> 00:00:36,050
Here are two sound self-investments that will pay handsome profits in the years ahead.

8
00:00:36,079 --> 00:00:37,250
1.

9
00:00:37,759 --> 00:00:39,650
Invest in education.

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,690
True education is the soundest investment you can make in yourself.

11
00:00:44,879 --> 00:00:48,849
But let's be sure we understand what education really is.

12
00:00:49,359 --> 00:00:55,409
Some folks measure education by the number of years spent in school or the number of diplomas,

13
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:57,970
certificates, and degrees earned.

14
00:00:58,399 --> 00:01:04,530
But this quantitative approach to education doesn't necessarily produce a successful person.

15
00:01:04,719 --> 00:01:13,009
Ralph J. Cordner, chairman of General Electric, expressed the attitude of top business management toward education this way.

16
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:20,929
Two of our most outstanding presidents, Mr. Wilson and Mr. Coffin, never had an opportunity to attend college.

17
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:28,449
Although some of our present officers have doctor's degrees, 12 out of 41 have no college degrees.

18
00:01:28,879 --> 00:01:32,449
We are interested in competency, not diplomas.

19
00:01:32,879 --> 00:01:39,650
A diploma or degree may help you get a job, but it will not guarantee your progress on the job.

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:44,210
Business is interested in competency, not diplomas.

21
00:01:44,719 --> 00:01:51,010
To others, education means the quantity of information a person has stashed away in his brain.

22
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:56,369
But the soak-up-facts method of education won't get you where you want to go.

23
00:01:57,599 --> 00:02:03,090
More and more we depend on books, files and machines to warehouse information.

24
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:07,730
If we can do only what a machine can do, we're in a real fix.

25
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:15,170
Real education, the kind worth investing in, is that which develops and cultivates your mind.

26
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:20,849
How well educated a person is, is measured by how well his mind is developed,

27
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:23,889
in brief, by how well he thinks.

28
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:31,970
Anything that improves thinking ability is education, and you can obtain education in many ways,

29
00:02:32,159 --> 00:02:37,090
but the most efficient sources of education for most people are nearby colleges and universities.
